Reasoning: The paper presents distributed algorithms for edge-coloring in graphs, which is a problem in distributed computing and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves the study of graph structures and their properties, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The algorithms presented in the paper involve the use of randomness and deterministic techniques, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
